  "texts": [
    "The sensitivity of decoder-only models to prompt variations and the order of class presentation further highlighted their susceptibility to contextual nuances, potentially impacting their sentiment analysis performance.",
    "One notable drawback emerged in the form of latency, with decoder-only models exhibiting significantly slower processing times compared to their encoder-only counterparts.",
    "This substantial difference, spanning two to three orders of magnitude, underscores the efficiency challenges associated with decoder-only architectures.The results from this work resonate with the findings across various studies.",
    "As [21] highlights the suitability of decoder-only for simple tasks but challenges in more complex scenarios, the present work aligns by showcasing how encoder-only models excel in NLU, prioritizing efficiency for practical applications.",
    "Moreover, the emphasis on few-shot learning and limited training data mirrors the acknowledgment in this study that decoder-only models can be expedient alternatives, particularly under fine-tuning constraints."
  ],
